<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-086-668  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 086 668.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 27 1989 v6 n8 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Not a 'necessary evil,' but a valuable resource. (Documentation)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miskie, Ronald.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Vendors must recognize the need for proper documentation and seeit as a beneficial, results-producing tool, not a 'necessaryevil.' Inadequate product documentation costs companies millionsof dollars.andP;  Instructional materials and operations manuals aretoo often written in technical terms when they should be writtenfrom a user's perspective.andP;  Documentation and training link designand implementation and must not frustrate a user.andP;  Gooddocumentation can be a sales tool as well as a support andtraining tool.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DocumentationCritiqueUser TrainingTechnical Writing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>